<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="1063" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1063">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.51/9–1345: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-13T19:00:00-04:00">September
                                    13, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>302. Dept informed by Exim Bank that on Sept 10 Paraguay paid $37,850.
                            The account is now fully paid to Aug 31 with the exception of
                            approximately $1700 representing interest on past due principal.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>